02:42.205 --> 02:45.034
So, I suppose I'll
see you after class?

02:45.077 --> 02:47.210
I suppose you will.

02:47.254 --> 02:50.126
Now, didn't she used to
walk you to your seat?

02:50.170 --> 02:51.997
She did,
but she was younger then.

02:52.041 --> 02:54.174
That makes sense.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.611
Sheldon and Billy
are friends.

02:56.654 --> 02:58.743
My son should be at his party.

02:58.787 --> 03:00.615
Look,

03:00.658 --> 03:03.139
I'm not trying
to be mean here.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.620
Billy has a tough enough
time with other kids

03:05.663 --> 03:08.579
without them seeing him pal
around with the local weirdo.

03:08.623 --> 03:10.668
I thought you weren't
trying to be mean.

03:10.712 --> 03:12.844
That was the nicest
way I could say it.

03:12.888 --> 03:16.108
Well, I'm not trying
to be mean here either,

03:16.152 --> 03:20.069
but you are behaving
very unneighborly.

03:20.112 --> 03:21.984
That was mean?

03:22.027 --> 03:24.247
You're darn tootin'.Tootin'?

03:24.291 --> 03:26.945
Tootin'!
Okay.

03:26.989 --> 03:29.948
So if Einstein's analysis
of time is correct,

03:29.992 --> 03:31.776
the future's already happened,

03:31.820 --> 03:34.866
but we'll discuss that
in more detail next week.

03:34.910 --> 03:38.087
Or perhaps we already have.Exactly.

03:38.130 --> 03:40.307
Good one. Let's hit the road.

03:40.350 --> 03:41.612
It was nice seeing you, Connie.

03:41.656 --> 03:45.268
Uh, we should get coffee
sometime and catch up.

03:45.312 --> 03:49.577
Maybe, sure, yeah. We'll see.

03:49.620 --> 03:51.535
What about, uh,
tomorrow morning?

03:51.579 --> 03:54.408
Oh, that's not great for me.

03:54.451 --> 03:56.975
Well, what about Sunday?

03:57.019 --> 03:59.891
Mm, I can't do that either.
Maybe another time.

03:59.935 --> 04:02.851
Oh, I see.

04:02.894 --> 04:04.156
You should probably settle

04:04.200 --> 04:06.115
