more than football and grapes.

13:26.893 --> 13:30.113
Why don't you head on
in to the den, John?

13:32.376 --> 13:33.856
You, get lost.

13:33.900 --> 13:37.077
So you two can feed
each other grapes? Got it.

13:43.997 --> 13:46.826
Hmm. Gallus gallus domesticus,

13:46.869 --> 13:49.785
otherwise known
as "Earth chicken."

13:49.829 --> 13:53.484
Live long and prosper...
you filthy bird.

13:55.269 --> 13:57.053
I thought you
didn't like chickens.

13:57.097 --> 13:58.576
Sheldon doesn't
like chickens.

13:58.620 --> 14:00.665
Mr. Spock finds them
fascinating.

14:00.709 --> 14:03.668
Who's Mr. Spock?I'm Mr. Spock.

14:03.712 --> 14:05.627
I'm Billy.

14:05.670 --> 14:06.715
What you doing?

14:06.758 --> 14:08.630
Using my tricorder
to collect data.

14:08.673 --> 14:10.501
What's a tricorder?

14:10.545 --> 14:12.112
It's a multifunctional
handheld device

14:12.155 --> 14:13.896
used for scanning
and analysis.

14:13.940 --> 14:17.073
Cool. And what's everything
you just said?

14:17.117 --> 14:20.076
Fascinating.

14:23.601 --> 14:26.909
George, would you
prefer me to wait

14:26.953 --> 14:28.345
for a commercial break

14:28.389 --> 14:31.696
before I bring up
my emotional state?

14:31.740 --> 14:34.569
Oh, still want
to talk about that, huh?

14:34.612 --> 14:35.657
Well, I...

14:35.700 --> 14:38.312
do think it would be
helpful for me.

14:38.355 --> 14:42.316
Uh, we got seven minutes
till kickoff.

14:42.359 --> 14:44.796
Have at it.Where to begin?

14:44.840 --> 14:48.278
I saw Connie for the first time
since I broke up with her,

14:48.322 --> 14:51.064
and it was harder
than I expected.

14:51.107 --> 14:53.109
Well, breakups can be rough.

14:53.153 --> 14:55.633
I thought I was doing
the right thing by her,

14:55.677 --> 14:58.201
but now it seems
that I've lost her,

14:58.245 --> 15:01.944
not only as a romantic partner,
but even as a friend.

15:01.988 --> 15:04.773
Women, huh?I've been feeling

15:04.816 --> 15:08.211
the loss very profoundly
and it's making me wonder

15:08.255 --> 15:10.474
if she also is feeling lonely

15:10.518 --> 15:13.825
and I made a bad decision
for both of us.

15:16.350 --> 15:18.656
I hate to be the one
to tell you this, John,

15:18.700 --> 15:21.050
but, uh...

15:21.094 --> 15:23.444
she's kind of been
seeing someone new

15:23.487 --> 15:25.446
and, uh...

15:25.489 --> 15:27.622
she seems to be
doing okay.

15:27.665 --> 15:31.278
I see.

15:33.019 --> 15:34.455
Is she happy?

15:34.498 --> 15:37.632
Hard to tell.
Her face is all scrunched up

15:37.675 --> 15:39.939
and pinched
most of the time.

15:39.982 --> 15:43.855
Well, I hope this man she's
seeing treats her well.

15:45.031 --> 15:46.423
He seems okay.

15:46.467 --> 15:50.036
I also hope he gets lost
at sea and never returns.

15:51.341 --> 15:54.214
I'm having a lot
of feelings.

15:54.257 --> 15:56.956
Well, when that happens to me,
I have another beer.

15:56.999 --> 15:59.567
I haven't finished
this one yet.

15:59.610 --> 16:00.872
More for me.

16:02.657 --> 16:05.790
Ensign Sparks, there appears
to be a white object

16:05.834 --> 16:08.576
under this chicken.It's called an egg.

16:08.619 --> 16:11.709
Interesting. What is its
function on this planet?

16:11.753 --> 16:15.496
People eat them and throw them
at me on Halloween.

16:15.539 --> 16:17.846
What are you doing out here?

16:17.889 --> 16:19.326
Playing with Sheldon.

16:19.369 --> 16:20.849
You're missing your party.

16:20.892 --> 16:22.329
But I'm having fun.

16:22.372 --> 16:24.679
Do not be alarmed,
our mission is one of peace.

16:24.722 --> 16:28.074
I'm gonna go have a little chat
with your mother.

16:29.640 --> 16:31.773
Seems unlikely;
my mother's on Vulcan.

16:31.816 --> 16:33.818
My mom is on Valium.

16:47.702 --> 16:50.270
Oh, they scored
another touchdown.

16:50.313 --> 16:52.446
That's just
a replay, John.

16:55.927 --> 16:58.974
Hey.Connie.

16:59.018 --> 17:01.716
I saw your bike outside,
so I-I thought I'd just,

17:01.759 --> 17:04.675
uh, say hi.

17:04.719 --> 17:06.460
Well, that's so nice of you.

17:06.503 --> 17:08.549
I don't mean to interrupt
or anything.

17:08.592 --> 17:12.248
I just wanted to... check in.

17:13.684 --> 17:15.991
Would it be awkward
if I asked her to join us?

17:16.035 --> 17:18.733
Oh, couldn't be
any more awkward.

17:18.776 --> 17:21.388
Would you like to, uh,
watch the game with us?

17:21.431 --> 17:22.824
It's-it's football.

17:22.867 --> 17:25.348
Well, sure.

17:25.392 --> 17:26.784
I guess a...

17:26.828 --> 17:28.830
little visit wouldn't hurt.

17:30.136 --> 17:32.225
Excellent.

17:32.268 --> 17:35.489
Let me guess,
you brought the grapes.

17:35.532 --> 17:37.665
I did.

17:43.236 --> 17:44.759
Hey, how many of those
have you had?

17:44.802 --> 17:46.674
So many!

17:49.198 --> 17:50.939
Hope you're happy.

17:50.982 --> 17:53.724
Billy's missing his own party
'cause he's playing spaceman

17:53.768 --> 17:55.813
in the chicken coop
with your son.

17:58.251 --> 18:01.123
You were right. I shouldn't have
made you invite him.

18:01.167 --> 18:02.385
I'm sorry.

18:05.084 --> 18:07.216
Okay.

18:07.260 --> 18:09.566
Well, good.

18:09.610 --> 18:13.266
It's just hard
to see him be left out.

18:13.309 --> 18:16.965
And I worry it's not gonna
get better when he grows older.

18:19.185 --> 18:22.275
Can't say that Billy
is exactly Mr. Popular either.

18:24.320 --> 18:26.279
I'm sure this kind of stuff
bothers me

18:26.322 --> 18:28.107
way more than
it bothers Sheldon.

18:31.501 --> 18:33.503
Doesn't make it any easier,
does it?

18:33.547 --> 18:35.897
No.

18:35.940 --> 18:37.986
I'm gonna take Shelly back home

18:38.029 --> 18:41.598
so that Billy can
get back to his party.
Eh.

18:41.642 --> 18:44.297
You know, they're
having fun out there.

18:45.863 --> 18:48.257
SHELDON:
Gallus gallus domesticus
pooped on my uniform!

18:48.301 --> 18:50.912
The mission
is compromised!

18:51.956 --> 18:54.133
Maybe take him home.Yeah.

18:59.399 --> 19:02.228
I've got something here for
both of you. It's from Billy.

19:02.271 --> 19:04.186
I hope it's not
another invitation.

19:04.230 --> 19:06.797
It's probably a thank you note.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.669
So now I have to write
a you're welcome note?

19:08.712 --> 19:10.236
You people are killing me.

19:10.279 --> 19:11.541
"Dear Sheldon
and Missy,

19:11.585 --> 19:13.195
"thank you for coming
to my party.

19:13.239 --> 19:15.023
"I liked playing with Mr. Spock

19:15.066 --> 19:17.286
and watching Missy throw up
Kool-Aid in the bushes."

19:17.330 --> 19:19.245
Still tasted like cherry.

19:19.288 --> 19:22.944
"My mother also threw up,
but that was because of wine.

19:22.987 --> 19:25.512
My dad says she
drinks because..."Okay, that's nice.

19:25.555 --> 19:27.992
But there's more.No, there's not.

19:28.036 --> 19:30.952
Guess we'll never know
why she drinks.

